Rendering Pattern:

![alt text](image.png)
![alt text](image-1.png)

Hydration -> means it adds listeners to the web page for interactions after javascript got rendered on the screen.

![alt text](image-2.png)

In CSR, initially browser is going to load html from client side. https://github.com/namastedev/namaste-frontend-system-design/blob/master/Performance/RenderingPatterns/page-router/src/pages/csr-page.js

In SSR, server is going to load html from server then the hydration will happen. https://github.com/namastedev/namaste-frontend-system-design/blob/master/Performance/RenderingPatterns/page-router/src/pages/ssr-page.js

In SSG, at the time of build itself it'll create a static site, when the browser hits it instantly gives, this can be used for blogs and for static sites where data won't change overtime.
![alt text](image-3.png). https://github.com/namastedev/namaste-frontend-system-design/blob/master/Performance/RenderingPatterns/page-router/src/pages/ssg-page.js

